definition: to pull/to play (a bowed instrument)/to drag/to draw/to chat

sentences.english: The blouse Niu that unties her buttons up, will her sleep the position that the skirt pulls Gao Dao's loins.
sentences.chinese: 解开她的上衣纽扣，将她的睡裙拉高到腰部的位置。

sentences.english: When you lift your foot, you are using your same-side shinbone as a long lever.
sentences.chinese: 当你的脚被拉高时，胫骨就变成了一个长长的杠杆。

sentences.english: Nope … the volume is too high for that. BTW, why would they?
sentences.chinese: 老大不会觉得是机构拉高准备出货？

sentences.english: Could you lift up your shirt? Did you eat anything yesterday?
sentences.chinese: 请你把衬衫拉高，昨天你吃了什么东西吗？

sentences.english: So Japanese locals bring assets back into JPY.
sentences.chinese: 所以日本本地资产将日元拉高。
